  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "These were the cities appointed for all the children of Israel,.... For the common use of them all, and not for that tribe only in which they stood: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and for the stranger that sojourneth among them; not only for the proselytes of righteousness, but for the proselytes of the gate also, as well as for the natives of Israel; Christ is a refuge for Jews and Gentiles, for all sinners that flee to him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that whosoever killeth any person unawares might flee thither; and find shelter and safety: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and not die by the hand of the avenger of blood; getting thither before he could overtake him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "until he stood before the congregation: either before the congregation, the elders of the city, or court of judicature in the city of refuge, or before the court of his own city, from whence he fled, if summoned thither. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "until he stood before the congregation: either before the congregation, the elders of the city, or court of judicature in the city of refuge, or before the court of his own city, from whence he fled, if summoned thither. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
